In Florida males are mature for most of the year except March, while females spawn between April and December (
Borkowski 1971
). In the field spawning occurs whenever the tide rises above MHWS, and not on a lunar rhythm; in the laboratory it was found to be induced by splash (
Borkowski 1971
). Size-frequency data suggest settlement from January to March in 
Jamaica
(

Lang 
et al
. 1998

), and growth rates have been measured in Florida (
Borkowski 1974
).
